Compute $\\arctan 1 + \\arctan \\frac{1}:
The addition formula for angle sums for tangent is 
\[\tan (\theta_1 + \theta_2)= \frac{\tan \theta_1 + \tan \theta_2}{1-\tan \theta_1 \cdot \tan \theta_2} . \]
This allows us to compute that
\begin{align*}
\tan (\arctan 1 + \arctan \frac{1}{2}) &= \frac{1+\frac{1}{2}}{1-1 \cdot\frac{1}{2}}= \frac{3}{2},
\end{align*}
then 
\begin{align*}
\tan (\arctan 1 + \arctan \frac{1}{2} + \arctan \frac{1}{3}) &= \frac{\frac{3}{2}+\frac{1}{3}}{1-\frac{3}{2} \cdot\frac{1}{3}}=1.
\end{align*}
The angle whose tangent is 1 is $\frac{\pi}{4}.$ Therefore, $\arctan 1 + \arctan \frac{1}{2} + \arctan \frac{1}{3} = \boxed{\frac{\pi}{4}}.$

Since $\tan \frac{\pi}{4} = 1,$ we know that $\arctan 1 = \frac{\pi}{4}.$

